disableSpokeCaliber.t.sol
├── when call is reentrant
│  └── it should revert with ReentrancyGuardReentrantCall
└── when call is not reentrant
   ├── when caller does not have the relevant role
   │  └── it should revert with AccessManagedUnauthorized
   └── when caller has the relevant role
      ├── given no spoke caliber is registered in this contract for the provided chain ID
      │  └── it should revert with InvalidChainId
      └── given a spoke caliber is registered in this contract for the provided chain ID
         ├── given the spoke caliber is already disabled
         │  └── it should revert with AlreadyDisabled
         └── given the spoke caliber is not already disabled
            ├── when the spoke caliber net AUM is non-zero as per the current accounting data
            │  └── it should revert with CaliberNotEmpty
            └── when the spoke caliber net AUM is zero as per the current accounting data
               ├── when there are pending bridge transfers from this contract to spoke caliber
               │  └── it should revert with PendingBridgeTransfer
               └── when there are no pending bridge transfers from this contract to spoke caliber
                  ├── when there are pending bridge transfers from spoke caliber to this contract as per the current accounting data
                  │  └── it should revert with PendingBridgeTransfer
                  └── when there are no pending bridge transfers from spoke caliber to this contract as per the current accounting data
                     ├── it should mark the spoke caliber as disabled
                     └── it should emit a SpokeCaliberDisabled event
